body.description: Always on the go? Baby Trend has you covered! The Rocket Plus Lightweight Stroller is equipped with an ultra-lightweight frame that offers easy strolling and effortless mobility when on the go. This stroller includes a canopy and visor to protect your child from the sun, as well as a 5-point harness to keep them safe and comfortable. Not only will baby be comfy, you will experience comfort as well with the soft grip handles, and convenience with the parent organizer and cupholders for easy accessibility to your on-the-go essentials. For even more convenience when your hands are full, this stroller includes a large storage basket for all of your traveling necessities. The Rocket Plus is equipped with dual-rear brakes that are foot activated and allows for stability and safety while out and about. This stroller offers a lightweight and compact fold for hassle-free travel or storage when not in use.

Quality. Baby Trend offers products at top tier quality that are durable and safe for baby. All products meet and exceed US safety standards and will keep your child safe and secure. Our products are simple to use with added features to help get the job done so you can easily enjoy your little one! Comfort. Here at Baby Trend, our top priority is that your child is comfortable and happy when using our products! With plush fabrics and easy adjustability, your little one will be safe and comfortable at all times. We also want to ensure parents are comfortable while using our products with features like easy grip handles and innovative parent trays. Comfort not only for baby, but for the whole family! Style. Style is a must at Baby Trend! With unique colors, textures, and patterns, you will love the way our products look in your house, your car, or when out and about. You will not only love what our products have to offer, but the way they look as well! Baby Trend has distinguished itself among the worldwide manufacturers of juvenile products. Throughout the 30 year history of our company, we have been on the forefront of new and innovative solutions that meet the ever increasing demands of new parents. We strive to accomplish this feat by adhering to our goal of providing safe, reliable products. We continually tailor our products as the challenges facing families change and grow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Loving this stroller!!
reviews.reviewText: I like that it’s light and the wheels roll very smooth. My 2 year old fits comfortably and I love that the foot rest can be adjusted to flat when he is sleeping or down while he is awake.We had a summer lite stroller and a jeep powergyled both of those strollers wheels would get stuck and they were hard to turn in my opinion. This stroller surprised me and excelled my expectations. Lightweight,sturdy, spacious, and wheels work great! It folds easily as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have to say this is one of the best purchases I’ve made in a long time.I am little and I have the hardest time transporting and opening and closing our large jogger stroller. I often rent strollers for outrageous prices when I go places like the zoo. Finally I looked for a light weight stroller. I wanted something better than the cheaper umbrella strollers I see some of my friends have. This is perfect. It’s easy to fold. Light weight. Fits in my compact cars trunk. Love the black on black color. It comes with an amazing attachment with two cup holders and zip storage. I wish that I always had this stroller.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good basic stroller
reviews.reviewText: This is a good stroller for the price. We needed something that was lightweight and could fold up small, but wanted something more sturdy than a traditional umbrella stroller. This is exactly that. No extra fluff. The sun visor is a waste and provides absolutely no shade. We took it off because it just made it bulkier when folded and didn’t serve a purpose. The stroller is very difficult to close, but does fold up nicely, just like an umbrella stroller. I keep this in my car for times when I didn’t think to pack the big stroller. It is perfect for shopping because it is small and maneuverable compared to my full size stroller. My daughter is about 33 pounds and 37 inches tall. She fits fine, but probably won’t be able to use it much longer. She does look a little snug in it. My biggest complaint is the clip to hold it closed when folded did not work. It was on there and intact, but the opening was so small, it would not clamp on the bar like it was supposed to.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this stroller for my 17 month old baby that loves being taken on walks. I didn’t have a stroller so this time when looking for one I was looking for a small, lightweight, easy to store away, easy to take up the stairs and back down, and comfortable for me and baby. And this is the perfect one for me and my baby. I love that it has cup holders and is washable, I love that I can easily recline his seat back for when he sleeps, and it fits in the car without taking so much space (which is what my mans loved as well).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Perfect size but basket kept breaking
reviews.reviewText: I love that this stroller was so lightweight and compact. I was also impressed with how smooth the ride was for such a small stroller. Closing it was not the best design but the major flaw is the basket underneath. The basket broke the first time on both sides and we exchanged it for a new one. The new one broke within a couple days on one side. We opted to just return it and get a different brand. If we didn’t use the basket underneath for storage I would have kept it, but our little guy stills needs too much stuff when we go out to be without it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Push button for wheel is just hiding in the frame
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE!! The push pin was just pushed up inside of the frame so it couldnt be seen. Finagled it out and now the stroller is perfect! Babytrend customer service helped by pointing this out.I purchased a "like new" one that was $12 cheaper than new and it arrived with the back stroller legs sticking out of a hole in the box. One of the metal push pins that holds the back wheel on is missing. Not sure if this happened in transit to me or if it was overlooked when it was previously returned and shipped out to me defective. I contacted babytrend using the link Amazon provided and haven't heard anything back in a week. Seems like a nice enough umbrella stroller for the price point. I like the zippered parent pouch and that the sun shade can be moved higher for an older child. We've been trying it around the house (carefully so the back wheel doesn't pop off) with my 30 lb 2 year old my 4 year old (can't remember his weight but he's tall). The front wheels sometimes just slide sideways but hoping that's just because it's not getting traction on the vinyl flooring. I would stay away from the previously returned ones if you're considering it but new would be a good value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2018
reviews.reviewText: I love this stroller! We can go off the trail with this no problem! I love the adjustable settings for the chair itself and the handles. The only thing I don’t like is that it’s not very compact and a bit of a task getting it in & out of the car. Just because you need to break it down but I’ve gotten used to it and it’s no big deal! It is a bit wide and doesn’t always fit in some places I need to go but it still beats using an umbrella stroller! Also, the storage space underneath is perfect!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Return this it was too small for my 2 years old
Poor quality, heavy and bulky mechanisms! Closure complicated with sharp metal clips.

reviews.reviewTitle: 某テーマパークに使用。
reviews.reviewText: 3歳児、18キロ。歩くのイヤイヤマン。某テーマパークに行くのに購入しました。安定性もあり、子供も乗り降りが楽なようで、大助かりでした。
遠出の際、一日中歩き疲れた5歳児が乗ったり、ショッピングのあと荷物を乗せたりして使っています。コンパクトに簡単に折りたためるし、ドリンクフォルダーも付いているし、小さなジップ付き収納もあるので便利。ティッシュやウェットティッシュをいつでも使えるようにしまって使っています。便利です。
もうちょっと屋根の機能性を高めて欲しかった。あと深く座ることが出来ないので、ベルトをしないと、落ちそうになる。16キロの息子、まだまだ使うので安心です。

reviews.reviewTitle: 普段使いはおすすめできません。
reviews.reviewText: ４歳娘のディズニーランド用に購入。ほかの方のレビューにありましたが日よけのサイズが意味不明です。下についている小物入れもすぐ切れました。折り畳みもしづらいです。４歳児以上が乗れるベビーカーの選択肢が自分では見つからなかったのでこちらを購入しましたががんばって他のを探せばよかったと後悔。。。
